277
00:21:02,592 --> 00:21:04,240
But they disowned me.

278
00:21:07,220 --> 00:21:08,540
They told me to get out because I'm gay.

279
00:21:08,540 --> 00:21:10,540
They said I wasn't their child anymore.

280
00:21:11,720 --> 00:21:13,126
What about you, Keito?

281
00:21:13,151 --> 00:21:14,831
Do you have a family?

282
00:21:15,520 --> 00:21:17,700
I have my mom.

283
00:21:18,160 --> 00:21:20,960
Your mom. Tell me about her.

284
00:21:22,453 --> 00:21:23,600
It's a secret.

285
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:25,900
What kind of person is she? Your mom?

286
00:21:27,560 --> 00:21:29,500
A secret is a secret.

287
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:35,860
That face...

288
00:21:37,220 --> 00:21:38,680
It's so gentle...

289
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:42,940
You can make that kind of face too...

290
00:21:45,520 --> 00:21:46,700
Keito.

291
00:21:47,660 --> 00:21:50,780
- Think about your mom.
- Huh?

292
00:21:51,880 --> 00:21:52,980
Alright.

293
00:22:06,920 --> 00:22:08,360
- Hey!
- Ah!

294
00:22:09,951 --> 00:22:12,271
I think your face got covered!

295
00:22:14,560 --> 00:22:16,060
Forget it.

296
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:18,540
Let's go.

297
00:22:19,360 --> 00:22:22,620
Such a waste! It was a good shot.

298
00:22:23,560 --> 00:22:25,020
Oh well.

299
00:22:41,780 --> 00:22:44,160
Aren't you going to work tomorrow?

300
00:22:45,100 --> 00:22:46,300
Maybe.

301
00:22:46,800 --> 00:22:47,760
Why?

302
00:22:49,240 --> 00:22:50,732
I don't know what to think

303
00:22:50,748 --> 00:22:52,428
about when I'm alone.

304
00:22:54,490 --> 00:22:55,638
When I space out,

305
00:22:55,662 --> 00:22:58,129
all I can think about are bad things,

306
00:22:59,440 --> 00:23:00,820
and I feel like dying.

307
00:23:16,580 --> 00:23:17,500
What?

308
00:23:18,640 --> 00:23:19,880
Then let's do it.

309
00:23:20,814 --> 00:23:22,056
That way, you won't have to

310
00:23:22,081 --> 00:23:23,298
think about anything.

311
00:24:01,460 --> 00:24:03,300
Yeah but...

312
00:24:07,160 --> 00:24:09,280
are you going to do it with me?

313
00:24:10,680 --> 00:24:11,960
You're not used to this?

314
00:24:13,700 --> 00:24:14,800
No,

315
00:24:16,160 --> 00:24:18,340
it's not that I don't like it...

316
00:24:27,020 --> 00:24:28,520
You make cute sounds.

317
00:24:38,060 --> 00:24:40,600
I don't know why I was drawn to Keito.

318
00:24:41,840 --> 00:24:43,386
Maybe he was the chocolate

319
00:24:43,403 --> 00:24:45,325
I found at the end of my ruined life.

320
00:24:46,832 --> 00:24:48,535
I don't know if this is the start of

321
00:24:48,535 --> 00:24:50,340
happiness or the beginning of hell,

322
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:53,600
but that chocolate was bitter;

323
00:24:55,380 --> 00:24:57,300
oh so sweet.

324
00:25:00,040 --> 00:25:01,820
(Next episode)

325
00:25:03,620 --> 00:25:05,580
I've been here for two weeks.

326
00:25:05,612 --> 00:25:07,292
Can I still stay here?

327
00:25:07,340 --> 00:25:08,960
If you want to continue to stay.

328
00:25:12,080 --> 00:25:13,880
What? Why did you suddenly cling to me?

329
00:25:13,880 --> 00:25:15,180
"Happy of the End"
